04/05/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- Energy Minister Taner Yildiz said on Tuesday (May 3rd) that his country and Iran are working on a new roadmap aimed to boost energy investments. During a joint press conference with Iranian counterpart Majid Namjou in Ankara, Yildiz said Ankara and Tehran have agreed to establish technical committees to pave the way for investments in the private sector, particularly in the field of renewable energy. Namjou said the roadmap would help double energy exchange capacity between the two countries. (Xinhua, IRNA, Anadolu news agency - 03/05/11)
